<br>
  I am a relatively new player and the skald is the first class I tried.  I have a great time with him and except for the resistance chants cant seem to find that much wrong with the class.  Imo the skald can be a viable class if played correctly both for pve and rvr.  <br>
<br>
 The skald is not a main tank and never will be.  Nor is it intended to be a caster.  We are a hybrid.  As a hybrid conventional wisdom as to how to play doesn't seem to apply.  Convention wisdom seems to be the same as to how to play and what RAs to get.  We aren't all melee so toe to toe seems like a bad idea.  We aren't casters so we cant stand back and nuke.  We do not have high hitpoints.  We die fast in rvr. <br>
<br>
 So what do we do?<br>
<br>
I originally started as a pen and paper roleplayer.  I have played 5 different mmorpg (daoc being the 5th).  In all of these games the challenge was to find a way to make a class effective.  I love hybrids for just this reason.  In D&amp;D I always played the fighter mage.  In Eq I played a beastlord (best hybrid ever).  Here I play the skald.  If I wanted to rule in melee I would be full fighter.  If I wanted to nuke I would be full mage.  With the skald I do it all and no matter the reason ppl are glad to see my speeding over the hill.<br>
<br>
 As a hybrid class alterations in play style need to be made.  Not so much in game mechanics as perhaps in how the skald is percieved and played.  Mini maxing seems to be the answer to many of the rvr issues which with 1.61 seems a more viable solution.  The removal of stat caps means that we can start to build a character designed around front loaded damage.  Given this concept the troll skald seems the most suited.  Getting the max amount of strength + highest damage add + high weapon specc seems to be the answer.  Or at least worth looking into <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  RA that give strength and con with MoP also seem like a possible solution.  If the Rains stacked with our damage add I would want to max one of those out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  With our hitpoints we cannot expect to live long but in the huge zergs I see here no one does either. :P In the course of my gaming I will try to post what RA I get how they work and if any combo helps me hit that little bit harder.  Anything to make those caster cry 'EEK' and run!<br>
<br>
The first stategy that pops into my mind is all about the speed.  Hide by a road run in really fast hit as hard as possible snare hit dd dd mez hit.  May not work havent had time to try it yet. Expect to die if you do it on anything other than 1v1.  Before you say this sucks keep in mind the assassins almost invarialbly get killed after striking in a group.<br>
The second idea is of course the classic kiting.  snare dd dd mez run repeat.  Will take a long time to kill anything but man will they hate you!  This I think would be best used on a tank.  Not like they could actually catch a careful skald <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
Any other ideas for skald stategies please post here I would appreciate it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am by no means an experienced DAoC player.  I do not pretend that I know all there is to know about the skald or the game.  Niether do I think I'm qualified to tell someone else how they should play (wouldn't want to in any case).  I do think that the real challenge to the class is that it takes more skill and forethought than your average melee or caster to play.  <br>
<br>
But in any case this is a game and this is for fun.  Best way to treat it in my opinion.  So have FUN with it! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>I taste like Menthol.<br>
<br>
I am refreshingly different; some people don't appreciate that. My sharp honesty gets up some people's noses, while others really enjoy it. I am something of an acquired taste.<br>
